oss section is small but much larger than the neutrino floor lying in the\nrange $\\sim (1-10)\\times 10^{-47}$ cm$^{2}$. Thus a significant part of the\nparameter space of the model will lie within the reach of the next generation\nLUX-ZEPLIN dark matter experiment.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 15 Mar 2016 20:00:03 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 10 May 2016 16:45:39 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-06-01"}
