iched when the galaxies\ncoalesce. This is the first time that such ISM enrichment at the final\ncoalescence stage is observed, which demonstrates the importance of supernova\nexplosion in affecting the nuclear metallicity. Meanwhile the central SFR\nenhancement relative to the control sample evolves simultaneously with the\nnuclear gas-phase oxygen abundance. Our results support the predictions from\nnumerical simulations.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 16 Mar 2016 08:21:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2016-06-21"}
